Make Socio-Economic Indices for Areas lookup table

Source: R/fn_make.R
make_seifa_lup.Rd

make_seifa_lup() is a Make function that creates a new R object. Specifically, this function implements an algorithm to make socio-economic indices for areas lookup table. The function returns Socio-Economic Indices for Areas (a lookup table).

make_seifa_lup(
  url_1L_chr = character(0),
  fl_nm_1L_chr = character(0),
  col_nms_chr = c("postcode_dbl", "score_dbl", "percentile_dbl"),
  consent_1L_chr = "",
  keep_cols_int = c(1, 3, 7),
  sheet_1L_int = 3L,
  percentile_var_nm_1L_chr = "percentile_dbl",
  quartile_var_nm_1L_chr = "quartile_dbl",
  range_1L_chr = "A6:Q2635",
  write_to_1L_chr = character(0)
)

Arguments

url_1L_chr

Url (a character vector of length one), Default: character(0)

fl_nm_1L_chr

File name (a character vector of length one), Default: character(0)

col_nms_chr

Column names (a character vector), Default: c("postcode_dbl", "score_dbl", "percentile_dbl")

consent_1L_chr

Consent (a character vector of length one), Default: ''

keep_cols_int

Keep columns (an integer vector), Default: c(1, 3, 7)

sheet_1L_int

Sheet (an integer vector of length one), Default: 3

percentile_var_nm_1L_chr

Percentile variable name (a character vector of length one), Default: 'percentile_dbl'

quartile_var_nm_1L_chr

Quartile variable name (a character vector of length one), Default: 'quartile_dbl'

range_1L_chr

Range (a character vector of length one), Default: 'A6:Q2635'

write_to_1L_chr

Write to (a character vector of length one), Default: character(0)

Value

Socio-Economic Indices for Areas (a lookup table)
